# GitHub API Token
# Required for GitHubEmbed component to fetch repository data at build time
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored)
# 2. Get token: https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
# 3. Scope: public_repo (read-only access to public repositories)
# 4. Paste token below
#
# CLOUDFLARE CI/CD:
# Store the token as a GitHub Secret (Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions)
# The build command will automatically pass it as GITHUB_TOKEN
#
# Rate limits:
# - Without token: 60 requests/hour (GitHub API limit for unauthenticated)
# - With token: 5000 requests/hour
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here
